<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Distribution.</emphasis>
Cosmopolitan species; usually found in areas near warm seas of Atlantic, Pacific, Indian Oceans, from Mediterranean Sea to 
<collectingRegion box="[555,656,188,213]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Southern" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Southern</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry box="[663,730,188,213]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Easton" box="[745,890,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Easton, E. G. (1984) Earthworms (Oligochaeta) from islands of the south - western Pacific, and a note on two species from Papua New Guinea. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 11 (2), 111 - 128. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1984.10423750" type="journal article" year="1984">Easton 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Blakemore" box="[901,1086,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Blakemore, R. J. (2002) Cosmopolitan Earthworms - an Eco - Taxonomic Guide to the Peregrine Species of the World. 2 nd Ed. VermEcology, PO BOX 414 Kippax, ACT 2615, Australia. August, 2002." type="journal article" year="2002">Blakemore 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Blakemore" box="[1100,1171,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Blakemore, R. J. (2007 b) Origin and means of dispersal of cosmopolitan Pontodrilus litoralis (Oligochaeta: Megascolecidae). European Journal of Soil Biology, 43, S 3 - 8. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ejsobi. 2007.08.041" type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="b">2007b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,416,223,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Vietnamese name.</emphasis>
Giun 
<taxonomicName box="[485,613,223,248]" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Pontodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="10" pageNumber="90" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">pontodrilus</taxonomicName>
vùng triều.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is usually found in coastal regions. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[963,1116,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Chen, Y. (1938) Oligochaeta from Hainan, Kwangtung. Contributions from the Biological Laboratory of the Science Society of China, Zoological Series, 12 (10), 375 - 427." type="journal article" year="1938">Chen (1938)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Iizuka, 1898" authorityName="Iizuka" authorityYear="1898" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Pontodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="matsushimensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pontodrilus matsushimensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Iizuka" box="[340,486,295,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Iizuka, A. (1898) On a new species of littoral Oligochaeta (Pontodrilus matshushimensis). Annotationes Zoologicae Japonenses, 2, 21 - 28." type="journal article" year="1898">Iizuka, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Beddard, 1891" authorityName="Beddard" authorityYear="1891" box="[563,925,295,320]" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Pontodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bermudensis">
<emphasis box="[563,737,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. bermudensis</emphasis>
Beddard, 1891
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Easton" box="[943,1107,296,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Easton, E. G. (1984) Earthworms (Oligochaeta) from islands of the south - western Pacific, and a note on two species from Papua New Guinea. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 11 (2), 111 - 128. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1984.10423750" type="journal article" year="1984">Easton (1984)</bibRefCitation>
considered both species as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grube, 1855" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1855" box="[302,586,332,357]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbricidae" genus="Lumbricus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="litoralis">
<emphasis box="[302,418,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. litoralis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Grube" box="[433,578,332,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Grube, E. (1855) Beschreibung neuer oder wenig bekannter Anneliden. Archiv Fur Naturgeschichte, 21, 81 - 136. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 13989" type="journal article" year="1855">Grube, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
